  "description": "Department naming and tier map for AI Workforce Blueprint v2.3 (26-department standard). Mandatory departments auto-build for every company (standard-unless-declined). Each vertical pack has a universal_primary department (the first dept in auto_add_departments, marked universal_primary=true) that is auto-added to EVERY client regardless of industry \u2014 this is what makes 17+7+2=26 the universal floor. Remaining pack departments (universal_primary=false or absent) still require an industry keyword match and serve as flavor/extras on top of the 24. WS-4: wired into build-workforce.py apply_vertical_packs() and department-floor.py evaluate_floor(). Each vertical-pack department carries a base_suggested_roles file so it ships with real roles + SOPs and never hard-fails assert_dept_map_resolves; the Research dept's industry-analysis-specialist-mckinsey-style role refines it via the industry-org-design research manifest. Custom departments are added by owner request. Personal Assistant is now mandatory (floor raised to 24 \u2014 approved v10.15.42). General Task (catch-all routing fallback) + Project Architecture Office (PAO, project governance) added as mandatory depts, raising the floor to 26 (v11.1.0).",
